The paper discusses the implementation of Cooperative Scans, an optimization technique for database systems, in an industrial-strength database product. This falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new optimization technique called Predictive Buffer Management, which involves managing buffer usage based on predictions of future workload. This could fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and performance evaluation (cs.CR). The implementation of these techniques likely involves changes to the database system's codebase, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
